01/09/2006
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- Foreign Minister Miodrag Vlahovic sent a letter Wednesday (30 August) to NATO Secretary General Jaap de Hoop Scheffer requesting Montenegrin membership in NATO's Partnership for Peace (PfP) programme. Vlahovic stressed that Podgorica views NATO integration as a priority, adding that it would strengthen regional peace and stability. NATO may discuss the matter at its November summit in Riga. 
In other news, President Filip Vujanovic told a group of visiting US senators that Podgorica considers relations with Washington a "strategic interest". He also urged better economic ties and more US investment in Montenegro. (MINA, Vijesti, Pobjeda - 31/08/06; AP - 30/08/06)
